  "prompt": "How do I prepare for SSC CGL Tier 2 in English?",
  "response": "To prepare for SSC CGL Tier 2 English section, follow these strategies:\n\n1. Reading Comprehension\n- Practice reading passages from various sources\n- Develop speed reading skills\n- Focus on understanding context and main ideas\n- Practice answering comprehension questions\n\n2. Grammar\n- Study fundamental grammar rules\n- Learn parts of speech\n- Practice error spotting\n- Understand sentence structure\n- Focus on tenses, articles, prepositions\n\n3. Vocabulary\n- Read newspapers, magazines\n- Learn new words daily\n- Use vocabulary apps\n- Practice synonyms and antonyms\n- Study word roots and prefixes\n\n4. Recommended Books\n- Wren & Martin's English Grammar\n- Plinth to Paramount by Neetu Singh\n- Word Power Made Easy by Norman Lewis\n- Rakesh Yadav's English Grammar Book\n\n5. Practice Resources\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Mock tests\n- Online practice platforms\n- SSC CGL specific English guides\n\n6. Time Management\n- Practice time-bound mock tests\n- Develop solving strategies\n- Improve speed and accuracy\n\n7. Online Resources\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Exam preparation websites\n- Online mock tests\n\n8. Regular Practice and Revision\n\nConsistent practice and strategic preparation are key to success.",
